# Branch Workflow

When working on a branch **other than `main` or a release branch** (e.g. `release/*`, `v*`):

## Work in Progress

- Treat all changes as **work in progress** until the branch is finished and merged.
- No need to maintain backwards compatibility with new work added in the branch.
- No need to capture changelog entries for work done in the working branch.

## When This Applies

- User indicates they are on a feature/development branch
- Changes are unmerged and not yet deployed
- Branch will be merged to main at a later date

## Exceptions

- On `main` or release branches: maintain backwards compatibility and update CHANGELOG for user-facing changes.
- When the user explicitly asks for changelog or migration notes.
